    *   The function first checks `pcap_check_activated(p)`. If this returns true (meaning the handle `p` is already activated, e.g., `pcap_open_live` has been called with it and `pcap_loop` or `pcap_next_ex` has been invoked), the function will return `PCAP_ERROR_ACTIVATED`.
